news.title: Times Real Estate Conclave & Awards 2021 brings good news galore, best performers
Gurugram: Deficient infrastructure work in DLF-1 and 2 yet to begin
news.para: A team of senior officials, including the MCG chief engineer and superintending engineer and a councillor, visited the colonies on Thursday.

news.title: Gurugram: Vipul Lavanya road cut off by another builder, say residents
news.para: Since February this year, the residents have been raising their concerns after their society being cut off from rest of the city but they say that no measures were taken by the two builders.

news.title: Mumbai: After discount to builders, BMC reaps Rs 11,000 crore windfall on premiums
news.para: Over the past decade, the civic administration collected Rs 3,500-4,000 crore each year by way of premiums and other charges from builders.

news.title: After CAG censure, sub-leasing of group housing plots in Noida to stop
news.para: Division of group housing plots, one of the reasons identified by the Comptroller and Auditor General for Noida’s real estate problems, will no longer be allowed.A formal decision on this is likely at the next Noida Authority meeting.

news.title: Government notifies new rules for consumer commissions
news.para: ​The Centre has notified new rules to revise pecuniary jurisdiction for entertaining consumer complaints at district, state and national level commissions, a move aimed at fast disposal of cases.

news.title: 2022 to open doors for e-auction of builders' attached properties
news.para: Traditionally, the collector of a district had powers to attach movable and immovable properties under provisions of the Uttar Pradesh Revenue Code, 2006. However, the process to realise the amount was extremely complicated and tedious.

news.title: Delhi government extends 20% reduction in circle rates till June 2022
news.para: Revenue Minister Kailash Gahlot said, "The 20% reduction in circle rates for all categories announced by Delhi govt will continue till 30th June 2022. Under Hon'ble CM @ArvindKejriwal ji's guidance, we assure all Delhiites that we will continue to stand with our people in times of need."

news.title: China Evergrande shares fall after missing new coupon payments
news.para: Evergrande, whose $19 billion in international bonds are in cross-default after missing a deadline to pay coupons earlier this month, had new coupon payments worth $255 million due on Tuesday for its June 2023 and 2025 notes.

news.title: Lucknow civic body hikes budget to spruceup streetlight facility in city
news.para: The EC meeting was convened by Mayor Sanyukta Bhatia to revise budgetary allocations for various purposes after taking stock of the expenditure by the LMC during the current financial year so far.

news.title: Tamil Nadu: No more extension charges for new Tangedco meters
news.para: For instance, an apartment in Chennai, which is located a hundred metres away from an existing power line, paid .90,000 as extension cost for a new three-phase connection.

news.title: Chennai: Unauthorised portions of commercial building sealed at T Nagar
news.para: While planning permission was issued for construction of basement floor (partly shop and parking) and ground + three floors for a shopping complex, one more floor was added to the structure.

news.title: Gujarat HC orders Ahmedabad civic body not to evict Vasna slum dwellers
news.para: Thirty-five families from the slums filed a petition in the high court through advocate Manoj Shrimali, who submitted that they had made a representation on August 19 for alternative accommodation after the civic body decided to demolish the slums.

news.title: TNUHDB may scrap allotments of owners who rented out flats
news.para: The board officials said they have the provisions to penalize the owners of the houses given on rent and would also cancel their allotments.

news.title: Nashik civic body to act tough against property tax defaulters
news.para: The civic body has set a property tax collection target of Rs 140 crore for the current financial year, but so far has managed to collect only Rs 107 crore.
